{
  "texts": [
    "First, the image is preprocessed using patch division (Fig. 2), and then several transformer layers are applied (see details in Fig.",
    "3 and Fig. 4).",
    "The final step consists in a simple fully connected neural network for classification.mechanisms, which can be found in [12,13].",
    "At a high level, transformers are neural networks that use an attention mechanism that takes into account the global context while processing the entire input data element-wise.",
    "For visual recognition or text understanding, the context of each element is vital, and the transformer can capture more global correlations between parts of the sentence or the image compared to convolutional neural networks without an attention mechanism [9]."
  ]
}